The police in Ekiti State has arraigned a 32-year-old cleric, OpeyemiSunday, before an Ado-Ekiti magistrate's court for stealing amotorcycle.The police prosecutor, Caleb Leranmo, told the court Sunday stole aBajaj Boxer motorcycle belonging to one Yusuf Seyi, arguing that hisaction contravened Section 390 of the Criminal Code, Cap C 16, Vol. 1,Laws of Ekiti State, 2012.Sunday, however, pleaded not guilty and his counsel, TimileyinOmotosho, urged the court to grant him bail.The magistrate, Ade Lawal, granted the accused bail of N50,000 withtwo sureties depositing N50,000 each and adjourned the case untilSeptember 11.